gn=center|115\n|align=center|10\n|align=center|105\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2017}}\n|[[Tijana Bogi\u0107evi\u0107]]\n|English\n|\"[[In Too Deep (Tijana Bogi\u0107evi\u0107 song)|In Too Deep]]\"\n|colspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|11\n|align=center|98\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2018}}\n|[[Sanja Ili\u0107]] & [[Balkanika]]\n|Serbian{{efn|name=rs|Contains some phrases in the [[Torlakian dialect]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://quartzy.qz.com/1276064/everything-you-need-to-know-about-eurovision-and-its-decades-of-glorious-camp/|title=Everything you need to know about Eurovision\u2014and its decades of glorious camp|accessdate=13 May 2018}}</ref>}}\n|\"[[Nova deca]]\" {{small|(\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u0434\u0435\u0446\u0430)}}\n|align=center|19\n|align=center|113\n|align=center|9\n|align=center|117\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2019}}\n|[[Nevena Bo\u017eovi\u0107]]\n|Serbian{{Efn|Contains phrases in English.}}\n|\"[[Kruna (song)|Kruna]]\" {{small|(\u041a\u0440\u0443\u043d\u0430)}}\n|align=center|18\n|align=center|89\n|align=center|7\n|align=center|156\n|-bgcolor=\"#87A96B\"\n|{{N/A|{{Escyr|2020}}}}{{Efn|2020 contest was cancelled due to 2019-20 pandemic of Coronavirus.}}\n|[[Hurricane (Serbian band)|Hurricane]]\n|Serbian{{efn|name=rs2|Contains some phrases in English and Spanish.}}\n|\"[[Hasta la vista (Hurricane song)|Hasta la vista]]\"\n|colspan=\"4\" {{N/A|Cancelled}}\n|}\n\n==Hostings==\n\n<!-- DO NOT add flagicons to the host city column.  This article is already about Serbia, so there is no need to highlight with {{flagicon}} that the city is in the Serbia. This is in accordance with [[WP:ICONDECORATION]]. -->\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|- \n! Year\n! Location\n! Venue\n! Presenters\n! Image\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2008}}\n| [[Belgrade]]\n| [[Belgrade Arena]]\n| [[Jovana Jankovi\u0107]] and [[\u017deljko Joksimovi\u0107]]\n| [[File:ESC 2008 - Presenters at the 1st semifinal.jpg|98px]]\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n===Marcel Bezen\u00e7on Awards===\n{{further|Marcel Bezen\u00e7on Awards}}\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"font-size: 95%\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Category\n!Performer\n!Song\n!width=45px|Final\n!width=45px|Points\n!Host city\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| {{escyr|2007}}\n|Artistic Award\n|[[Marija \u0160erifovi\u0107]]\n|\"[[Molitva]]\" {{small|(\u041c\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0432\u0430)}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| 268\n|{{flagicon|Finland}} [[Helsinki]]\n|{{center|<ref>{{cite web|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190716092347/https://eurovision.tv/about/in-depth/marcel-bezencon-awards/|archive-date=16 July 2019|url=https://eurovision.tv/about/in-depth/marcel-bezencon-awards/|title=Marcel Bezen\u00e7on Awards|accessdate=8 December 2019|url-status=live|website=eurovision.tv}}</ref>}}\n|}\n\n===Winner by OGAE members===\n{{further|OGAE}}\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"font-size: 95%\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Song\n!Performer\n!width=45px|Final\n!width=45px|Points\n!Host city\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| {{escyr|2007}}\n|\"[[Molitva]]\" {{small|(\u041c\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0432\u0430)}}\n|[[Marija \u0160erifovi\u0107]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| 268\n|{{flagicon|Finland}} [[Helsinki]]\n|{{center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://escxtra.com/2017/04/21/analysing-ten-years-ogae-voting-underneath-fan-favourite-bias-worthwhile-indicator/|title=Analysing ten years of OGAE voting: \u201cUnderneath the fan favourite bias is a worthwhile indicator\u201d|website=escxtra.com|date=21 April 2017|accessdate=8 December 2019|first=Ryan|last=Cobb}}</ref>}}\n|}\n\n===Barbara Dex Award===\n{{further|Barbara Dex Award}}\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!Year\n!Performer\n!Host city\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2010}}\n|[[Milan Stankovi\u0107]]\n|{{flagicon|Norway}} [[Oslo]]\n|{{center|<ref name=\"barbara dex\">{{cite web|url=https://wiwibloggs.com/2015/07/09/poll-worst-dressed-barbara-dex-award-winner/|title=Poll: Who was the worst dressed Barbara Dex Award winner?|publisher=Wiwibloggs|date=9 July 2015|accessdate=8 December 2019|first=William Lee|last=Adams}}</ref>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2013}}\n|[[Moje 3]]\n|{{flagicon|Sweden}} [[Malm\u00f6]]\n|{{center|<ref name=\"barbara dex\"/>}}\n|}\n\n==Commentators and spokespersons==\nAll the events were broadcast on [[RTS1]], except the {{Escyr|2013}} grand final, the {{Escyr|2015}} second semi-final, which were broadcast on [[RTS2]].\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Commentator\n!Spokesperson\n!class=\"unsortable\"|{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2007}}\n|[[Du\u0161ka Vu\u010dini\u0107-Lu\u010di\u0107]] ||Maja Nikoli\u0107 ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2008}}\n|[[Dragan Ili\u0107]], Mladen Popovi\u0107 ||[[Du\u0161ica Spasi\u0107]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.b92.net/text/3059/Eurosong%20finale/|title=Eurosong finale|publisher=b92.net|accessdate=2008-05-24}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2009}}\n|Dragan Ili\u0107 {{small|(semi-final 1)}}<br>Du\u0161ka Vu\u010dini\u0107-Lu\u010di\u0107 {{small|(semi-final 2, final)}}||[[Jovana Jankovi\u0107]] ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2010}}\n|Du\u0161ka Vu\u010dini\u0107-Lu\u010di\u0107 {{small|(semi-final 1, final)}}<br>Dragan Ili\u0107 {{small|(semi-final 2)}}||Maja Nikoli\u0107 ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2011}}\n|Marina Nikoli\u0107 {{small|(semi-final 1)}}<br>Dragan Ili\u0107 {{small|(semi-final 2)}}<br>Du\u0161ka Vu\u010dini\u0107-Lu\u010di\u0107 {{small|(final)}}||Du\u0161ica Spasi\u0107 ||<ref name=\"Pesma Evrovizije 2011\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rts.rs/page/tv/sr/story/20/RTS+1/887122/Pesma+Evrovizije+2011.html|title=Pesma Evrovizije 2011|date=8 May 2011|work=[[Radio Television of Serbia|RTS]]|accessdate=8 May 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2012}}\n||Dragan Ili\u0107 {{small|(semi-final 1)}}<br>Du\u0161ka Vu\u010dini\u0107-Lu\u010di\u0107 {{small|(semi-final 2, final)}}|| rowspan=\"2\" |Maja Nikoli\u0107 ||<ref name=\"Serbian broadcast\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rts.rs/page/tv/sr/story/20/RTS+1/1105042/Pesma+Evrovizije+2012.html |title=Pesma Evrovizije 2012 |work=RTS |language=Serbian |date=19 May 2012 |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120521040930/http://www.rts.rs/page/tv/sr/story/20/RTS+1/1105042/Pesma+Evrovizije+2012.html |archive-date=21 May 2012 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2013}}\n|Du\u0161ka Vu\u010dini\u0107-Lu\u010di\u0107 {{small|(semi-final 1)}}<br>Marina Nikoli\u0107 {{small|(semi-final 2)}}<br>[[Silvana Gruji\u0107]] {{small|(final)}}||<ref name=SerbCom>{{cite web|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->|script-title=sr:\u041f\u0435\u0441\u043c\u0430 \u0415\u0432\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0437\u0438\u0458\u0435 2013 \u2013 \u0434\u0440\u0443\u0433\u043e \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0443\u0444\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0435, \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043d\u043e\u0441|url=http://www.rts.rs/page/tv/ci/story/17/%D0%A0%D0%A2%D0%A1+1/1324362/%D0%9F%D0%B5%D1%81%D0%BC%D0%B0+%D0%95%D0%B2%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B8%D0%B7%D0%B8%D1%98%D0%B5+2013+-+%D0%B4%D1%80%D1%83%D0%B3%D0%BE+%D0%BF%D0%BE%D0%BB%D1%83%D1%84%D0%B8%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%B5%2C+%D0%BF%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%BE%D1%81.html|publisher=[[Radio Television of Serbia]]|language=Serbian|trans-title=Eurovision Song Contest 2013 \u2013 first semi-final|date=15 May 2013|accessdate=15 May 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130608055841/http://www.rts.rs/page/tv/ci/story/17/%D0%A0%D0%A2%D0%A1+1/1324362/%D0%9F%D0%B5%D1%81%D0%BC%D0%B0+%D0%95%D0%B2%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B8%D0%B7%D0%B8%D1%98%D0%B5+2013+-+%D0%B4%D1%80%D1%83%D0%B3%D0%BE+%D0%BF%D0%BE%D0%BB%D1%83%D1%84%D0%B8%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%B5,+%D0%BF%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%BE%D1%81.html|archive-date=8 June 2013|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->|script-title=sr:\u0424\u0438\u