]]\"\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|98\n|-style=\"background:silver;\"\n!{{Escyr|1972}}\n|English\n|[[The New Seekers]]\n|\"[[Beg, Steal or Borrow]]\"\n|align=center|2\n|align=center|114\n|-style=\"background:#cc9966;\"\n!{{Escyr|1973}}\n|English\n|Cliff Richard\n|\"[[Power to All Our Friends]]\"\n|align=center|3\n|align=center|123\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1974}}\n|English\n|[[Olivia Newton-John]]\n|\"[[Long Live Love (Olivia Newton-John song)|Long Live Love]]\"\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|14\n|-style=\"background:silver;\"\n!{{Escyr|1975}}\n|English\n|[[The Shadows]]\n|\"[[Let Me Be the One (Eurovision song)|Let Me Be the One]]\"\n|align=center|2\n|align=center|138\n|-style=\"background:gold;\"\n!{{Escyr|1976}}\n|English\n|[[Brotherhood of Man]]\n|\"[[Save Your Kisses for Me]]\"\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|164\n|-style=\"background:silver;\"\n!{{Escyr|1977}}\n|English\n|[[Lynsey de Paul]] & [[Mike Moran (music producer)|Mike Moran]]\n|\"[[Rock Bottom (Lynsey de Paul and Mike Moran song)|Rock Bottom]]\"\n|align=center|2\n|align=center|121{{Efn|During the voting sequence of the live show, several errors were made in the announcement of the scores, which were then adjusted after the broadcast. Both Greece and France duplicated scores, awarding the same points to multiple countries. From the Greek scores, the UK, Netherlands, Austria & Finland all had 1 point deducted after the contest and from the French scores, Austria, Germany, Israel, Italy & Portugal all had 1 point deducted. None of the adjustments affected the placing of any of the songs. The result had the UK losing 1 point from their broadcast total of 122 to a corrected score of 121.}}\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1978}}\n|English\n|[[Co-Co (band)|Co-Co]]\n|\"[[The Bad Old Days]]\"\n|align=center|11\n|align=center|61\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1979}}\n|English\n|[[Black Lace (band)|Black Lace]]\n|\"[[Mary Ann (Black Lace song)|Mary Ann]]\"\n|align=center|7\n|align=center|73\n|-style=\"background:#c96;\"\n!{{Escyr|1980}}\n|English\n|[[Prima Donna (band)|Prima Donna]]\n|\"[[Love Enough for Two]]\"\n|align=center|3\n|align=center|106\n|-style=\"background:gold;\"\n!{{Escyr|1981}}\n|English\n|[[Bucks Fizz (band)|Bucks Fizz]]\n|\"[[Making Your Mind Up]]\"\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|136\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1982}}\n|English\n|[[Bardo (band)|Bardo]]\n|\"[[One Step Further]]\"\n|align=center|7\n|align=center|76\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1983}}\n|English\n|[[Sweet Dreams (band)|Sweet Dreams]]\n|\"[[I'm Never Giving Up]]\"\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|79\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1984}}\n|English\n|[[Belle and the Devotions]]\n|\"[[Love Games (Belle and the Devotions song)|Love Games]]\"\n|align=center|7\n|align=center|63\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1985}}\n|English\n|[[Aeone|Vikki]]\n|\"[[Love Is (Vikki Watson song)|Love Is]]\"\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|100\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1986}}\n|English\n|[[Ryder (band)|Ryder]]\n|\"[[Runner in the Night]]\"\n|align=center|7\n|align=center|72\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1987}}\n|English\n|[[Rikki (British singer)|Rikki]]\n|\"[[Only the Light]]\"\n|align=center|13\n|align=center|47\n|-style=\"background:silver;\"\n!{{Escyr|1988}}\n|English\n|[[Scott Fitzgerald (singer)|Scott Fitzgerald]]\n|\"[[Go (Scott Fitzgerald song)|Go]]\"\n|align=center|2\n|align=center|136\n|-style=\"background:silver;\"\n!{{Escyr|1989}}\n|English\n|[[Live Report]]\n|\"[[Why Do I Always Get it Wrong?]]\"\n|align=center|2\n|align=center|130\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1990}}\n|English\n|[[Emma (Welsh singer)|Emma]]\n|\"[[Give a Little Love Back to the World]]\"\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|87\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1991}}\n|English\n|[[Samantha Janus]]\n|\"[[A Message to Your Heart]]\"\n|align=center|10\n|align=center|47\n|-style=\"background:silver;\"\n!{{Escyr|1992}}\n|English\n|[[Michael Ball]]\n|\"[[One Step Out of Time]]\"\n|align=center|2\n|align=center|139\n|-style=\"background:silver;\"\n!{{Escyr|1993}}\n|English\n|[[Sonia (singer)|Sonia]]\n|\"[[Better the Devil You Know (Sonia song)|Better the Devil You Know]]\"\n|align=center|2\n|align=center|164\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1994}}\n|English\n|[[Frances Ruffelle]]\n|\"[[Lonely Symphony (We Will Be Free)]]\"\n|align=center|10\n|align=center|63\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1995}}\n|English\n|[[Love City Groove]]\n|\"[[Love City Groove (song)|Love City Groove]]\"\n|align=center|10\n|align=center|76\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1996}}\n|English\n|[[Gina G]]\n|\"[[Ooh Aah... Just a Little Bit]]\"\n|align=center|8{{Efn|Spain originally gave its 6 points to Poland. After the broadcast, it was announced the Spanish voting spokesperson had wrongly pronounced 'Holland' instead of 'The Netherlands', which the voting moderator had assumed was 'Poland'. The mistake was corrected and the Dutch score was increased by 6 points, moving the nation above the UK into 7th place and demoting the UK to 8th.}}\n|align=center|77\n|style=\"background:#c96;\" align=center|3\n|style=\"background:#c96;\" align=center|153\n|-style=\"background:gold;\"\n!{{Escyr|1997}}\n|English\n|[[Katrina and the Waves]]\n|\"[[Love Shine a Light]]\"\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|227\n|colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"7\"  {{n/a|No semi-finals}}\n|-style=\"background:silver;\"\n!{{Escyr|1998}}\n|English\n|[[Imaani]]\n|\"[[Where Are You? (Imaani song)|Where Are You?]]\"\n|align=center|2\n|align=center|166{{Efn|Spain originally gave its 12 points to Israel and 10 to Norway. After the broadcast it was announced that Spanish broadcaster wrongly tallied the votes and Germany should have got the top mark - 12 points - instead of being snubbed, as it happened. The mistake was corrected and so Germany was placed 7th over Norway. Israel and Norway both received 2 points less than originally and Croatia, Malta, Portugal, United Kingdom, Netherlands, Belgium, Estonia and Turkey all received one point less than indicated during the broadcast.}}\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1999}}\n|English\n|[[Precious (band)|Precious]]\n|\"[[Say It Again (Precious song)|Say It Again]]\"\n|align=center|12\n|align=center|38\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2000}}\n|English\n|[[Nicki French]]\n|\"[[Don't Play That Song Again]]\"\